Key Match Events: Stephen Curry hit two clutch 3-pointers, the second followed by his signature 'night night' celebration in the Warriors' 127-116 victory over the Thunder.
Stephen Curry scored a season-high 36 points in 36 minutes.
Jonathan Kuminga scored 12 points in the second quarter, helping the Warriors turn a seven-point deficit into a seven-point lead.
Stephen Curry scored 17 points on 7-for-10 shooting in the third quarter, nearly outscoring the Thunder by himself.
The Warriors scored a season-high 42 points in the third quarter, doubling up Oklahoma City (21 points).
De'Anthony Melton had his highest scoring output as a Warrior, finishing with 19 points, and grabbed 10 rebounds and recorded three steals.
Draymond Green dished out a game-high 11 assists, generating 25 points for the Warriors.
